12682]},{"content":"However, the provisioning profile expires after 1 year.","pos":[12683,12738]},{"content":"With this update, Intune gives you the tools to proactively deploy a new provisioning profile policy to devices that have apps that are near expiry while the certificate is still valid.","pos":[12739,12924]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Use iOS mobile provisioning profile policies to keep your line of business apps up to date<ept id=\"p1\">](/intune/deploy-use/ios-mobile-app-provisioning-profiles)</ept>.","pos":[12925,13101],"source":" For more information, see [Use iOS mobile provisioning profile policies to keep your line of business apps up to date](/intune/deploy-use/ios-mobile-app-provisioning-profiles)."},{"pos":[13129,13169],"content":"Xamarin SDK for Intune apps is available","linkify":"Xamarin SDK for Intune apps is available","nodes":[{"content":"Xamarin SDK for Intune apps is available","pos":[0,40]}]},{"content":"The Intune App SDK Xamarin component allows you to enable the Intune mobile app management features in your mobile iOS and Android apps built with Xamarin.","pos":[13170,13325]},{"content":"You can find the component in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Xamarin store<ept id=\"p1\">](https://components.xamarin.com/view/Microsoft.Intune.MAM)</ept> or on the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Microsoft Intune Github page<ept id=\"p2\">](https://github.com/msintuneappsdk)</ept>.","pos":[13326,13510],"source":" You can find the component in the [Xamarin store](https://components.xamarin.com/view/Microsoft.Intune.MAM) or on the [Microsoft Intune Github page](https://github.com/msintuneappsdk)."},{"pos":[13539,13556],"content":"Device management","linkify":"Device management","nodes":[{"content":"Device management","pos":[0,17]}]},{"pos":[13562,13596],"content":"Increased device enrollment limits","linkify":"Increased device enrollment limits","nodes":[{"content":"Increased device enrollment limits","pos":[0,34]}]},{"content":"Intune 