ce":" Use the instructions in the [Create and deploy mobile app management policies](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/mt627829.aspx) topic to create a MAM policy."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Mobile app configuration policies give you more flexibility to specify user details for iOS apps<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> You can supply user settings that an iOS app might need when it is opened.","pos":[41840,42015],"source":"**Mobile app configuration policies give you more flexibility to specify user details for iOS apps**\nYou can supply user settings that an iOS app might need when it is opened."},{"content":"For example, you can supply a network port, or a user name.","pos":[42016,42075]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configure iOS apps with mobile app configuration policies in Microsoft Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](configure-ios-apps-with-mobile-app-configuration-policies-in-microsoft-intune.md)</ept>.","pos":[42076,42255],"source":" For details, see [Configure iOS apps with mobile app configuration policies in Microsoft Intune](configure-ios-apps-with-mobile-app-configuration-policies-in-microsoft-intune.md)."},{"pos":[42260,42475],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Deploy Adobe Reader for Microsoft Intune to Intune-managed iOS devices in your enterprise<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> The Adobe Reader app for iOS can now be managed on enrolled devices with the Intune mobile application management policy.","source":"**Deploy Adobe Reader for Microsoft Intune to Intune-managed iOS devices in your enterprise**\nThe Adobe Reader app for iOS can now be managed on enrolled devices with the Intune mobile application management policy."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Ensure deployed web clips are opened in the managed browser<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> You can deploy targeted web clips that can only be opened using the managed browser on iOS and Android devices.","pos":[42479,42654],"source":"**Ensure deployed web clips are opened in the managed browser**\nYou can deploy targeted web clips that can only be opened using the managed browser on iOS and Android devices."},{"content":"For example, you deploy links to corporate resources through the Company Portal, and when users navigate to the links, they open directly into the managed browser where they can be protected by MAM policy.","pos":[42655,42860]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deploy apps <ept id=\"p1\">](deploy-apps.md)</ept>.","pos":[42861,42909],"source":" For details, see [Deploy apps ](deploy-apps.md)."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Find, manage, and distribute Windows Store for Business apps for Windows 10 devices from the Intune administrator console<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Support for Windows Store for Business is available in Intune to help you find, manage, and distribute apps to the Windows 10 devices you’re managing.","pos":[42914,43190],"source":"**Find, manage, and distribute Windows Store for Business apps for Windows 10 devices from the Intune administrator console**\nSupport for Windows Store for Business is available in Intune to help you find, manage, and distribute apps to the Windows 10 devices you’re managing."},{"content":"Windows Store for Business lets you manage the process of deploying and monitoring these apps from the Intune administrator console—the same console you use to manage your other apps.","pos":[43191,43374]},{"content":"Specifically, Windows Store for Business manages the content and licensing  of “online licensed apps”.","pos":[43375,43477]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Manage apps you purchased from the Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">](manage-apps-you-purchased-from-the-windows-store-for-business-with-microsoft-intune.md)</ept>.","pos":[43478,43647],"source":" For details, see [Manage apps you purchased from the Windows Store for Business](manage-apps-you-purchased-from-the-windows-store-for-business-with-microsoft-intune.md)."},{"pos":[43654,43671],"content":"Device management","linkify":"Device management","nodes":[{"content":"Device management","pos":[0,17]}]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>PFX certificates distribution for iOS devices<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Intune administrators can create and deploy iOS PFX certificates for Wi-Fi, email, and VPN authentication on iOS devices.","pos":[43674,43845],"source":"**PFX certificates distribution for iOS devices**\nIntune administrators can create and deploy iOS PFX certificates for Wi-Fi, email, and VPN authentication on iOS devices."},{"content":"This feature is already available for Android and Windows 10 devices.","pos":[43846,43915]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Enable access to company resources using certificate profiles <ept id=\"p1\">](secure-resource-access-with-certificate-profiles.md)</ept>.","pos":[43916,44051],"source":" For details, see [Enable access to company resources using certificate profiles ](secure-resource-access-with-certificate-profiles.md)."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Apply apps and policies to different device groups based on user category selection<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Intune administrators can now define custom device categories for users to select from during enrollment.","pos":[44056,44249],"source":"**Apply apps and policies to different device groups based on user category selection**\nIntune administrators can now define custom device categories for users to select from during enrollment."},{"content":"For example, administrators might want their users to specify if they're enrolling a device used for the \"Cash Register\" or \"Delivery Truck\" or \"Inventory Room.\"","pos":[44250,44411]},{"content":"The category selected will cause the device to become a member of an Intune device group, which can be used for deploying different apps and policies to the enrolled device.","pos":[44412,44585]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Categorize devices with device group mapping<ept id=\"p1\">](catego